1. install node js
2. make a project folder
3. Run npm init -y for create package.json file(package.json holds all the informations of the projects and packages)
4. install express js (express js is the framework of node js)
5. npm install express
6. create a file (exp:- server.js)
7. if we use any of packages then import the package in the top of the file(exp:- const express = require("express"))
8. if we use any of files then import the file in the top of the file with exact file path
9. if use the package then create a instance of the package (exp:- const app = express())
10. create a server (exp:- app.listen(7777,() => {
                                    console.log("server is running");
                                });
                                )
11. 
